    "By considering influence in expectation, Downsampling addresses LOO's inaccuracy caused by stochastic training's implicit variance.",
    "In practice, K, n, and m are finite.",
    "Nonetheless, Feldman & Zhang (2020, Lemma 2.1) prove that, with high probability, Downsampling's LOO influence estimation error is bounded given K and m n.",
    "While Downsampling's formulation above is w.r.t.",
    "a single training instance, Downsampling trivially extends to estimate the expected group influence of multiple training instances."
